We have some legacy fields from npm. I'm proposing this be the default layout:

``` json
{
  "name": "my-package",
  "main": "./lib/my-package",
  "version": "0.0.0",
  "description": "Meatballs",
  "repository":  "http://github.com/atom/my-package"
  "engines": {
    "atom": ">27.0"
  },
  "dependencies": {
    "temp": "0.6.0",
  }
}

I got rid of the `private` and `bugs` field and made `repository` point directly at the GitHub repo.
```
